    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 997.1 Carrera S is an exemplary specimen of Stuttgart engineering, maintained to a museum-grade standard. Power is delivered by the naturally aspirated 3.8L flat-six M97.01 engine, featuring a robust power band and crisp throttle response. The 6-speed manual transaxle offers precise gate engagement with no synchro wear. This chassis is equipped with Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM), providing exceptional lateral stability and damping control. Recent mechanical audits confirm zero bore scoring and a clean DME overrev report. The braking system retains its factory-spec bite via four-piston monoblock calipers and cross-drilled rotors. Every bushing, seal, and fluid line remains in peak operational condition, ensuring the communicative steering and telepathic handling these cars are known for.",
